ID: _dlqluuik9cmn0iphedt6ic0
Event: AgentForge Hackathon: Crafting Intelligent Assistants (June)
Description: Important reminders for attendees:
- Registration and breakfast start at 9:00 AM.
- Bring any necessary devices and materials for a full day of hacking.
- Food and drinks will be provided throughout the event.
- The event is for active builders with technical, machine learning, or entrepreneurial backgrounds working with large language models (LLMs) and generative AI.
- Attendance is screened to ensure a collaborative environment of experienced participants.

Event Overview:
The AgentForge Hackathon in Dublin is a full-day event focused on building intelligent, agentic AI assistants for various applications such as software development, healthcare, and finance. It is organized by AI Tinkerers, a community for practitioners working with foundation models like LLMs. The hackathon aims to connect like-minded builders in the Dublin area to foster innovation and collaboration.

Schedule:
- 9:00 AM - 9:30 AM: Registration & Breakfast
- 9:30 AM - 10:00 AM: Welcome & Opening Ceremony
- 10:00 AM - 12:30 PM: Hacking Session #1
- 12:30 PM - 1:30 PM: Lunch Break & Networking
- 1:30 PM - 3:00 PM: Hacking Session #2
- 3:00 PM - 3:15 PM: Coffee Break
- 3:15 PM - 5:30 PM: Hacking Session #3
- 5:30 PM - 6:30 PM: Final Project Submission, Wrap-up & Dinner
- 6:30 PM - 7:30 PM: Round One Judging
- 7:30 PM - 8:00 PM: Final Round Judging
- 8:00 PM - 8:45 PM: Finalist Presentations
- 8:45 PM - 9:00 PM: Awards Ceremony & Closing Remarks

About Agentic Assistants:
Agentic assistants are AI-driven tools designed to automate tasks such as customer support and operational workflows. They often include human-in-the-loop interactions for approvals and feedback and can integrate with platforms like Slack or command-line interfaces. These assistants leverage large language models to improve productivity and streamline processes.

Judges:
- Meji Abidoye, Co-founder at Abundant
- Ivo Garais, AI Engineer at Titanhq
- Niall Mahler, AI Innovation Engineering Leader at Marsh McLennan
- Shiv R, Product Manager at MasterCard
- Brendan Scullion, CTO at Coso.ai

Sponsors:
The event is supported by LangChain, an open-source framework that simplifies the development of AI applications.

For more details and registration, visit the event page.

ID: _dlqluuik9cmn0iphedt6ic0
Event: AgentForge Hackathon: Crafting Intelligent Assistants (June)
Description: Important reminders for attendees:
- Registration and breakfast start at 9:00 AM.
- Bring any necessary devices and materials for a full day of hacking.
- Food and drinks will be provided throughout the event.
- The event is for active builders with technical, machine learning, or entrepreneurial backgrounds working with large language models (LLMs) and generative AI.
- Attendance is screened to ensure a collaborative environment of experienced participants.

Event Overview:
The AgentForge Hackathon in Dublin is a full-day event focused on building intelligent, agentic AI assistants for various applications such as software development, healthcare, and finance. It is organized by AI Tinkerers, a community for practitioners working with foundation models like LLMs. The hackathon aims to connect like-minded builders in the Dublin area to foster innovation and collaboration.

Schedule:
- 9:00 AM - 9:30 AM: Registration & Breakfast
- 9:30 AM - 10:00 AM: Welcome & Opening Ceremony
- 10:00 AM - 12:30 PM: Hacking Session #1
- 12:30 PM - 1:30 PM: Lunch Break & Networking
- 1:30 PM - 3:00 PM: Hacking Session #2
- 3:00 PM - 3:15 PM: Coffee Break
- 3:15 PM - 5:30 PM: Hacking Session #3
- 5:30 PM - 6:30 PM: Final Project Submission, Wrap-up & Dinner
- 6:30 PM - 7:30 PM: Round One Judging
- 7:30 PM - 8:00 PM: Final Round Judging
- 8:00 PM - 8:45 PM: Finalist Presentations
- 8:45 PM - 9:00 PM: Awards Ceremony & Closing Remarks

About Agentic Assistants:
Agentic assistants are AI-driven tools designed to automate tasks such as customer support and operational workflows. They often include human-in-the-loop interactions for approvals and feedback and can integrate with platforms like Slack or command-line interfaces. These assistants leverage large language models to improve productivity and streamline processes.

Judges:
- Meji Abidoye, Co-founder at Abundant
- Ivo Garais, AI Engineer at Titanhq
- Niall Mahler, AI Innovation Engineering Leader at Marsh McLennan
- Shiv R, Product Manager at MasterCard
- Brendan Scullion, CTO at Coso.ai

Sponsors:
The event is supported by LangChain, an open-source framework that simplifies the development of AI applications.

For more details and registration, visit the event page.

End Time: 6/7/2025, 9:00:00 PM

ID: _dlqluuik9cmn0iphedt6ic0
Event: AgentForge Hackathon: Crafting Intelligent Assistants (June)
Description: Important reminders for attendees:
- Registration and breakfast start at 9:00 AM.
- Bring any necessary devices and materials for a full day of hacking.
- Food and drinks will be provided throughout the event.
- The event is for active builders with technical, machine learning, or entrepreneurial backgrounds working with large language models (LLMs) and generative AI.
- Attendance is screened to ensure a collaborative environment of experienced participants.

Event Overview:
The AgentForge Hackathon in Dublin is a full-day event focused on building intelligent, agentic AI assistants for various applications such as software development, healthcare, and finance. It is organized by AI Tinkerers, a community for practitioners working with foundation models like LLMs. The hackathon aims to connect like-minded builders in the Dublin area to foster innovation and collaboration.

Schedule:
- 9:00 AM - 9:30 AM: Registration & Breakfast
- 9:30 AM - 10:00 AM: Welcome & Opening Ceremony
- 10:00 AM - 12:30 PM: Hacking Session #1
- 12:30 PM - 1:30 PM: Lunch Break & Networking
- 1:30 PM - 3:00 PM: Hacking Session #2
- 3:00 PM - 3:15 PM: Coffee Break
- 3:15 PM - 5:30 PM: Hacking Session #3
- 5:30 PM - 6:30 PM: Final Project Submission, Wrap-up & Dinner
- 6:30 PM - 7:30 PM: Round One Judging
- 7:30 PM - 8:00 PM: Final Round Judging
- 8:00 PM - 8:45 PM: Finalist Presentations
- 8:45 PM - 9:00 PM: Awards Ceremony & Closing Remarks

About Agentic Assistants:
Agentic assistants are AI-driven tools designed to automate tasks such as customer support and operational workflows. They often include human-in-the-loop interactions for approvals and feedback and can integrate with platforms like Slack or command-line interfaces. These assistants leverage large language models to improve productivity and streamline processes.

Judges:
- Meji Abidoye, Co-founder at Abundant
- Ivo Garais, AI Engineer at Titanhq
- Niall Mahler, AI Innovation Engineering Leader at Marsh McLennan
- Shiv R, Product Manager at MasterCard
- Brendan Scullion, CTO at Coso.ai

Sponsors:
The event is supported by LangChain, an open-source framework that simplifies the development of AI applications.

For more details and registration, visit the event page.
Start Time: 6/7/2025, 9:00:00 AM
End Time: 6/7/2025, 9:00:00 PM
Attendees: h67dabhi@gmail.com

ID: _dlqluuik9cmn0iphedt6ic0
Event: AgentForge Hackathon: Crafting Intelligent Assistants (June)
Description: Important reminders for attendees:
- Registration and breakfast start at 9:00 AM.
- Bring any necessary devices and materials for a full day of hacking.
- Food and drinks will be provided throughout the event.
- The event is for active builders with technical, machine learning, or entrepreneurial backgrounds working with large language models (LLMs) and generative AI.
- Attendance is screened to ensure a collaborative environment of experienced participants.

Event Overview:
The AgentForge Hackathon in Dublin is a full-day event focused on building intelligent, agentic AI assistants for various applications such as software development, healthcare, and finance. It is organized by AI Tinkerers, a community for practitioners working with foundation models like LLMs. The hackathon aims to connect like-minded builders in the Dublin area to foster innovation and collaboration.

Schedule:
- 9:00 AM - 9:30 AM: Registration & Breakfast
- 9:30 AM - 10:00 AM: Welcome & Opening Ceremony
- 10:00 AM - 12:30 PM: Hacking Session #1
- 12:30 PM - 1:30 PM: Lunch Break & Networking
- 1:30 PM - 3:00 PM: Hacking Session #2
- 3:00 PM - 3:15 PM: Coffee Break
- 3:15 PM - 5:30 PM: Hacking Session #3
- 5:30 PM - 6:30 PM: Final Project Submission, Wrap-up & Dinner
- 6:30 PM - 7:30 PM: Round One Judging
- 7:30 PM - 8:00 PM: Final Round Judging
- 8:00 PM - 8:45 PM: Finalist Presentations
- 8:45 PM - 9:00 PM: Awards Ceremony & Closing Remarks

About Agentic Assistants:
Agentic assistants are AI-driven tools designed to automate tasks such as customer support and operational workflows. They often include human-in-the-loop interactions for approvals and feedback and can integrate with platforms like Slack or command-line interfaces. These assistants leverage large language models to improve productivity and streamline processes.

Judges:
- Meji Abidoye, Co-founder at Abundant
- Ivo Garais, AI Engineer at Titanhq
- Niall Mahler, AI Innovation Engineering Leader at Marsh McLennan
- Shiv R, Product Manager at MasterCard
- Brendan Scullion, CTO at Coso.ai

Sponsors:
The event is supported by LangChain, an open-source framework that simplifies the development of AI applications.

For more details and registration, visit the event page.

ID: _dlqluuik9cmn0iphedt6ic0
Event: AgentForge Hackathon: Crafting Intelligent Assistants (June)
Description: Important reminders for attendees:
- Registration and breakfast start at 9:00 AM.
- Bring any necessary devices and materials for a full day of hacking.
- Food and drinks will be provided throughout the event.
- The event is for active builders with technical, machine learning, or entrepreneurial backgrounds working with large language models (LLMs) and generative AI.
- Attendance is screened to ensure a collaborative environment of experienced participants.

Event Overview:
The AgentForge Hackathon in Dublin is a full-day event focused on building intelligent, agentic AI assistants for various applications such as software development, healthcare, and finance. It is organized by AI Tinkerers, a community for practitioners working with foundation models like LLMs. The hackathon aims to connect like-minded builders in the Dublin area to foster innovation and collaboration.

Schedule:
- 9:00 AM - 9:30 AM: Registration & Breakfast
- 9:30 AM - 10:00 AM: Welcome & Opening Ceremony
- 10:00 AM - 12:30 PM: Hacking Session #1
- 12:30 PM - 1:30 PM: Lunch Break & Networking
- 1:30 PM - 3:00 PM: Hacking Session #2
- 3:00 PM - 3:15 PM: Coffee Break
- 3:15 PM - 5:30 PM: Hacking Session #3
- 5:30 PM - 6:30 PM: Final Project Submission, Wrap-up & Dinner
- 6:30 PM - 7:30 PM: Round One Judging
- 7:30 PM - 8:00 PM: Final Round Judging
- 8:00 PM - 8:45 PM: Finalist Presentations
- 8:45 PM - 9:00 PM: Awards Ceremony & Closing Remarks

About Agentic Assistants:
Agentic assistants are AI-driven tools designed to automate tasks such as customer support and operational workflows. They often include human-in-the-loop interactions for approvals and feedback and can integrate with platforms like Slack or command-line interfaces. These assistants leverage large language models to improve productivity and streamline processes.

Judges:
- Meji Abidoye, Co-founder at Abundant
- Ivo Garais, AI Engineer at Titanhq
- Niall Mahler, AI Innovation Engineering Leader at Marsh McLennan
- Shiv R, Product Manager at MasterCard
- Brendan Scullion, CTO at Coso.ai

Sponsors:
The event is supported by LangChain, an open-source framework that simplifies the development of AI applications.

For more details and registration, visit the event page.

ID: _dlqluuik9cmn0iphedt6ic0
Event: AgentForge Hackathon: Crafting Intelligent Assistants (June)
Description: Important reminders for attendees:
- Registration and breakfast start at 9:00 AM.
- Bring any necessary devices and materials for a full day of hacking.
- Food and drinks will be provided throughout the event.
- The event is for active builders with technical, machine learning, or entrepreneurial backgrounds working with large language models (LLMs) and generative AI.
- Attendance is screened to ensure a collaborative environment of experienced participants.

Event Overview:
The AgentForge Hackathon in Dublin is a full-day event focused on building intelligent, agentic AI assistants for various applications such as software development, healthcare, and finance. It is organized by AI Tinkerers, a community for practitioners working with foundation models like LLMs. The hackathon aims to connect like-minded builders in the Dublin area to foster innovation and collaboration.

Schedule:
- 9:00 AM - 9:30 AM: Registration & Breakfast
- 9:30 AM - 10:00 AM: Welcome & Opening Ceremony
- 10:00 AM - 12:30 PM: Hacking Session #1
- 12:30 PM - 1:30 PM: Lunch Break & Networking
- 1:30 PM - 3:00 PM: Hacking Session #2
- 3:00 PM - 3:15 PM: Coffee Break
- 3:15 PM - 5:30 PM: Hacking Session #3
- 5:30 PM - 6:30 PM: Final Project Submission, Wrap-up & Dinner
- 6:30 PM - 7:30 PM: Round One Judging
- 7:30 PM - 8:00 PM: Final Round Judging
- 8:00 PM - 8:45 PM: Finalist Presentations
- 8:45 PM - 9:00 PM: Awards Ceremony & Closing Remarks

About Agentic Assistants:
Agentic assistants are AI-driven tools designed to automate tasks such as customer support and operational workflows. They often include human-in-the-loop interactions for approvals and feedback and can integrate with platforms like Slack or command-line interfaces. These assistants leverage large language models to improve productivity and streamline processes.

Judges:
- Meji Abidoye, Co-founder at Abundant
- Ivo Garais, AI Engineer at Titanhq
- Niall Mahler, AI Innovation Engineering Leader at Marsh McLennan
- Shiv R, Product Manager at MasterCard
- Brendan Scullion, CTO at Coso.ai

Sponsors:
The event is supported by LangChain, an open-source framework that simplifies the development of AI applications.

For more details and registration, visit the event page.

ID: _dlqluuik9cmn0iphedt6ic0
Event: AgentForge Hackathon: Crafting Intelligent Assistants (June)
Description: Important reminders for attendees:
- Registration and breakfast start at 9:00 AM.
- Bring any necessary devices and materials for a full day of hacking.
- Food and drinks will be provided throughout the event.
- The event is for active builders with technical, machine learning, or entrepreneurial backgrounds working with large language models (LLMs) and generative AI.
- Attendance is screened to ensure a collaborative environment of experienced participants.

Event Overview:
The AgentForge Hackathon in Dublin is a full-day event focused on building intelligent, agentic AI assistants for various applications such as software development, healthcare, and finance. It is organized by AI Tinkerers, a community for practitioners working with foundation models like LLMs. The hackathon aims to connect like-minded builders in the Dublin area to foster innovation and collaboration.

Schedule:
- 9:00 AM - 9:30 AM: Registration & Breakfast
- 9:30 AM - 10:00 AM: Welcome & Opening Ceremony
- 10:00 AM - 12:30 PM: Hacking Session #1
- 12:30 PM - 1:30 PM: Lunch Break & Networking
- 1:30 PM - 3:00 PM: Hacking Session #2
- 3:00 PM - 3:15 PM: Coffee Break
- 3:15 PM - 5:30 PM: Hacking Session #3
- 5:30 PM - 6:30 PM: Final Project Submission, Wrap-up & Dinner
- 6:30 PM - 7:30 PM: Round One Judging
- 7:30 PM - 8:00 PM: Final Round Judging
- 8:00 PM - 8:45 PM: Finalist Presentations
- 8:45 PM - 9:00 PM: Awards Ceremony & Closing Remarks

About Agentic Assistants:
Agentic assistants are AI-driven tools designed to automate tasks such as customer support and operational workflows. They often include human-in-the-loop interactions for approvals and feedback and can integrate with platforms like Slack or command-line interfaces. These assistants leverage large language models to improve productivity and streamline processes.

Judges:
- Meji Abidoye, Co-founder at Abundant
- Ivo Garais, AI Engineer at Titanhq
- Niall Mahler, AI Innovation Engineering Leader at Marsh McLennan
- Shiv R, Product Manager at MasterCard
- Brendan Scullion, CTO at Coso.ai

Sponsors:
The event is supported by LangChain, an open-source framework that simplifies the development of AI applications.

For more details and registration, visit the event page.

ID: _dlqluuik9cmn0iphedt6ic0
Event: AgentForge Hackathon: Crafting Intelligent Assistants (June)
Description: Important reminders for attendees:
- Registration and breakfast start at 9:00 AM.
- Bring any necessary devices and materials for a full day of hacking.
- Food and drinks will be provided throughout the event.
- The event is for active builders with technical, machine learning, or entrepreneurial backgrounds working with large language models (LLMs) and generative AI.
- Attendance is screened to ensure a collaborative environment of experienced participants.

Event Overview:
The AgentForge Hackathon in Dublin is a full-day event focused on building intelligent, agentic AI assistants for various applications such as software development, healthcare, and finance. It is organized by AI Tinkerers, a community for practitioners working with foundation models like LLMs. The hackathon aims to connect like-minded builders in the Dublin area to foster innovation and collaboration.

Schedule:
- 9:00 AM - 9:30 AM: Registration & Breakfast
- 9:30 AM - 10:00 AM: Welcome & Opening Ceremony
- 10:00 AM - 12:30 PM: Hacking Session #1
- 12:30 PM - 1:30 PM: Lunch Break & Networking
- 1:30 PM - 3:00 PM: Hacking Session #2
- 3:00 PM - 3:15 PM: Coffee Break
- 3:15 PM - 5:30 PM: Hacking Session #3
- 5:30 PM - 6:30 PM: Final Project Submission, Wrap-up & Dinner
- 6:30 PM - 7:30 PM: Round One Judging
- 7:30 PM - 8:00 PM: Final Round Judging
- 8:00 PM - 8:45 PM: Finalist Presentations
- 8:45 PM - 9:00 PM: Awards Ceremony & Closing Remarks

About Agentic Assistants:
Agentic assistants are AI-driven tools designed to automate tasks such as customer support and operational workflows. They often include human-in-the-loop interactions for approvals and feedback and can integrate with platforms like Slack or command-line interfaces. These assistants leverage large language models to improve productivity and streamline processes.

Judges:
- Meji Abidoye, Co-founder at Abundant
- Ivo Garais, AI Engineer at Titanhq
- Niall Mahler, AI Innovation Engineering Leader at Marsh McLennan
- Shiv R, Product Manager at MasterCard
- Brendan Scullion, CTO at Coso.ai

Sponsors:
The event is supported by LangChain, an open-source framework that simplifies the development of AI applications.

For more details and registration, visit the event page.

Event: AgentForge Hackathon: Crafting Intelligent Assistants (June)
Description: Important reminders for attendees:
- Registration and breakfast start at 9:00 AM.
- Bring any necessary devices and materials for a full day of hacking.
- Food and drinks will be provided throughout the event.
- The event is for active builders with technical, machine learning, or entrepreneurial backgrounds working with large language models (LLMs) and generative AI.
- Attendance is screened to ensure a collaborative environment of experienced participants.

Event Overview:
The AgentForge Hackathon in Dublin is a full-day event focused on building intelligent, agentic AI assistants for various applications such as software development, healthcare, and finance. It is organized by AI Tinkerers, a community for practitioners working with foundation models like LLMs. The hackathon aims to connect like-minded builders in the Dublin area to foster innovation and collaboration.

Schedule:
- 9:00 AM - 9:30 AM: Registration & Breakfast
- 9:30 AM - 10:00 AM: Welcome & Opening Ceremony
- 10:00 AM - 12:30 PM: Hacking Session #1
- 12:30 PM - 1:30 PM: Lunch Break & Networking
- 1:30 PM - 3:00 PM: Hacking Session #2
- 3:00 PM - 3:15 PM: Coffee Break
- 3:15 PM - 5:30 PM: Hacking Session #3
- 5:30 PM - 6:30 PM: Final Project Submission, Wrap-up & Dinner
- 6:30 PM - 7:30 PM: Round One Judging
- 7:30 PM - 8:00 PM: Final Round Judging
- 8:00 PM - 8:45 PM: Finalist Presentations
- 8:45 PM - 9:00 PM: Awards Ceremony & Closing Remarks

About Agentic Assistants:
Agentic assistants are AI-driven tools designed to automate tasks such as customer support and operational workflows. They often include human-in-the-loop interactions for approvals and feedback and can integrate with platforms like Slack or command-line interfaces. These assistants leverage large language models to improve productivity and streamline processes.

Judges:
- Meji Abidoye, Co-founder at Abundant
- Ivo Garais, AI Engineer at Titanhq
- Niall Mahler, AI Innovation Engineering Leader at Marsh McLennan
- Shiv R, Product Manager at MasterCard
- Brendan Scullion, CTO at Coso.ai

Sponsors:
The event is supported by LangChain, an open-source framework that simplifies the development of AI applications.

For more details and registration, visit the event page.
Start Time: 6/7/2025, 9:00:00 AM
End Time: 6/7/2025, 9:00:00 PM
